There is a potential race condition here as d.chains is not protected by lock. I think the old logic may have a problem to only check the request spatial layer, we can check if there is a decodable target that is lesser or equal to the request one like this:
```
for _, dt := range d.decodeTargets {
    if dt.Active && dt.Layer.Spatial < requestLayer && dt.Valid() {
        return true,layer
    }
}
